rning our use of natural language 'might' and 'might have' sentences, Steinberg finally argues that truths about objective chances are able to provide a supervenience base for modal truths.A Chance for Possibility is an investigation in analytic metaphysics, drawing on related work in the philosophy of logic and language as well as linguistics. It provides a detailed case study for the fruitful use of a notion of grounding in the clarification and evaluation of longstanding philosophical issues.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aModality (Logic) 0aModality (Logic). 0aPossibility. 0aRealism. 0aSupervenience (Philosophy) 0aSupervenience (Philosophy). 4aModal Logic. 4aModal Truth. 4aNatural Language. 4amodale Logik. 4amodale Wahrheit. 4anatürliche Sprache. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Language.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2013z978311031732908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2013z9783110317312oZDB-23-DPH0 cprintz978311033489040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110338232423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110338232.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031732-9  E-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2013b2013  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  